Chinese President Xi Jinping and US President Donald Trump had a productive meeting during Trump's state visit to China. They discussed various issues of shared interest and reached many common understandings. Both leaders emphasized the importance of China-US relations for the wellbeing of their peoples and the world. They agreed to further promote strategic guidance of summit diplomacy, strengthen interactions at all levels, and expand cooperation in areas such as economy and trade, military relations, law enforcement, and people-to-people exchange. They also discussed the nuclear issue on the Korean Peninsula and other major international and regional issues. Both leaders expressed their commitment to enhancing cooperation and managing differences in a spirit of mutual respect and mutual benefit. Trump praised their relationship and expressed optimism about the future of China-US relations. He also commended China's hosting of a military parade.